The apex of pronotal setae is also variable, most frequently expanded or capitate ( Figs 22 , 259 ), sometimes blunt ( Figs 27 , 169 ), and some species may have some setae acute (e.g.
H. stannardi
). Not all setae have the same type of apex, with smaller setae (usually am and/or aa) frequently having acute or blunt apex in contrast to the capitate tips of longer setae.
